        </p>
        <p>In this example, the user performs three transformations of the variable of interest. The first is a fractional polynomial transformation with one degree and a power of ‚àí‚Äâ2. The second transformation is a fractional polynomial transformation with four degrees and powers of 0.5,1,‚àí0.5, and 2. The third transformation is a fractional polynomial transformation with two degrees and powers of ‚àí‚Äâ0.5, and 1.</p>
